    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Polyhedrons having one face (the base) that is a polygon of any number of sides, and the other faces are triangles with bases forming the sides of the polygon meet at a common vertex.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
